oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Apollo 16 - Moon travel tapes - Tape 1 Side 3
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tape 1 (Side 3). Program sent on the Apollo 16 space mission for Charlie Duke's (astronaut) enjoyment. Originally from a cassette Tape. Tape featuring Bill Bailey (host), Buck Owens, Buck Owens & The Buckaroos, Susan Raye, and the Bakersfield Brass.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Bill Bailey; Buck Owens; Buckaroos; Buddy Owens; Susan Raye; Bakersfield Brass
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:03) Bill Bailey opening remarks addressing the Apollo 16 crew and introduces the Buck Owens -- (00:10) Mountain Dew (Buck Owens & The Buckaroos) -- (02:05) Buck Owens addresses Apollo 16 crew and introduces band members -- (03:50) Sam's Place (Buck Owens) -- (05:35) Buck Owens & The Buckaroos joke about astronauts and youth -- (06:45) Rolling in My Sweet Baby's Arms (Buck Owens) -- (08:49) Buck Owens addresses Charlie and resemblance. (09:58) White Lightning (Buddy Owens) -- (11:46) Georgia Pineywoods (Buck Owens) -- (13:30) Buck Owens & The Buckaroos jokes about Susan and Buddy playing chess -- (15:58) Happy Heart (Susan Raye) -- (17:40) Buck Owens jokes about drinking in space -- (18:50) Milwaukee Here I Come (Buck Owens & Susan Raye) -- (20:32) Buck Owens introduces the Bakersfield Brass and discusses space -- (22:12) Sally Was a Good Old Girl (Bakersfield Brass) -- (24:33) Buck Owens, Buddy Owens, & Susan Rayeaddresses astronauts wishing them best of luck -- (25:44) Tall Dark Stranger (Buck Owens) -- (27:23) Bill Bailey closing remarks
